Notes: Historical data in NGMM does not include re-exports of LNG
NGMM assumes all imports are from Canada

STEO includes liquefaction volumes in its pipeline and distribution use volumes where liquefaction is a seperate series in the NGMM. NGMM assumes a certain percentage of natural gas is consumed during LNG liquefaction, subtracts those volumes out of STEO's "Pipeline and Distribution Use" and assigns it to industrial consumption. After the liquefaction volumes are subtracted out, the series is benchmarked.
